    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Strings which have the upper edge notched, or otherwise worked to the shape of the steps, so that treads and risers are supported by and overlap the step-shaped edge.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000077471/Sturgis, Dictionary of Architecture and Building (1901)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Trapbomen met aan de bovenrand inkepingen of ander snijwerk in de vorm van de treden, zodat de aantreden en de optreden ondersteund worden door de tredevormige rand en deze overlappen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>上緣呈台階外形凹下的樓梯邊樑，階面及豎板隨著樑的邊緣疊置，並受邊樑支撐。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
